<div class="wrap">
	<h2>How to work with HTML5 Swiffy Insert</h2>
	<br />
	<strong>HTML5 Swiffy Insert</strong> is a simple plugin developed by Yuanga that lets you insert HTML5 animations generated with <a href="https://www.google.com/doubleclick/studio/swiffy/" target="_blank">Google Swiffy</a>. Swiffy converts Flash SWF files to HTML5, allowing you to reuse Flash content on devices without a Flash player (such as iPhones and iPads).
	<br /><br />
	To insert the generated code by Swiffy into your wordpress page or post, you have to follow these <strong>three</strong> steps:
	<br />
	<ol>
		<li>In the first lines of the HTML file source code generated by Swiffy (usually line number 9) you'll find a &lt;script&gt; tag starting by: <strong>swiffyobject =</strong>. Ok, you've to copy all the content of these script except the beginning (&lt;script&gt;swiffyobject =) and the end tag (&lt;/script&gt;). Don't be afraid! The loooooong code will be similar to: 
