		<li>In your editing page/post panel, scroll down to the area titled Custom Fields. Create a new Custom Field entering the text "<strong>swiffy_1</strong>" (without the quotes) in the text entry field titled <em>Name</em>, and type the code from the step 1 in the <em>Value</em> field. Click <strong>Add Custom Field</strong> button to save this custom information for that page. <br />
		<br /><strong>Note</strong>: Custom Fields may be hidden by default if they have not been used before. 
		<br /><strong>Note</strong>: If you need to include a second animation, you can add another custom field with the text "<strong>swiffy_2</strong>", and so on.</li>
		
		<li>Use a shortcode like this: 
		<blockquote>[swiffy n="1" w="550" h="400"]</blockquote>
		where:<br />
		<strong>n</strong> is the number of the animation, (1 by default, 2 for second animation on the same page...).<br />
		<strong>w</strong> is the width of the animation in pixels.<br />
		<strong>h</strong> is the height  of the animation in pixels.<br /><br />
		<strong>Note</strong>: If it's the first animation (<strong>swiffy_1</strong> defined in step number two) we use the shortcode: [swiffy n="1" w="550" h="400"]. If it's the second animation, <strong>n</strong> value will be 2.</li>
	</ol>
	Enjoy!
